Lagos State Governor, Babajide Sanwo-Olu, and the Minister of Information and Culture, Alhaji Lai Mohammed, are among dignitaries expected to attend the 49th Annual General Meeting/Congress of the Association of Advertising Agencies (AAAN). According to a statement by AAAN, the 49th AGM, themed, ‘The New World Order: Technology as a Game Changer’, will hold on Friday, July 22, 2022, at Jubilee Chalets, Epe, Lagos State. Sanwo-Olu is expected to declare the AGM open while Mohammed, whose ministry oversees advertising, will grace the event as Keynote Speaker as well as Special Guest of Honour. Other speakers at the event include, Mr. David Okeme (Executive Director, System Specs), Mr. Olu Akanmu (President/Co-CEO, Opay Nigeria), Mr. Adetayo Bamiduro (CEO/Cofounder Max.Ng), Mr. Niyi Yusuf (Managing Partner, Verraki Africa) and Mrs. Juliet Ehimuan-Chiazor (Google Country Manager). The following panelists are also expected: Mr. Norden Thurston, (Marketing Director, Seven Up), Mr. Kelechi Nwosu (MD, TBWA), Mr. Jay Chukwuemeka (Partner, Imaginarium) and Mrs. Ose Osundeko (COO, Digitas Nigeria). AAAN is the umbrella body of advertising agencies operating in Nigeria.